Movie "Desire for Love" (Polish: Chopin. Pragnienie mi≈Ço≈õci) is a film created by the director Jerzy Antczak based on the life story of the Polish pianist and composer Fr√©d√©ric Chopin.

The best pianist who performed Chopin Nocturnes was a Polish pianist Artur Rubinstein from Lodz, not far from the birthplace of Chopin-Zelazowa Wola,
He felt "that something" which is impossible to feel by non Polish pianists.
He was fiercely Polish, and great lover of Chopin music.
Throughout his life, Rubinstein was deeply attached to Poland. At the inauguration of the United Nations in 1945, Rubinstein showed his Polish patriotism at a concert for the delegates. He began the concert by stating his deep disappointment that the conference did not have a delegation from Poland. Rubinstein later described becoming overwhelmed by a blind fury and angrily pointing out to the public the absence of the Polish flag. He stopped playing the piano, told the audience to stand up, including the Soviets, and played the Polish national anthem loudly and slowly, repeating the final part in a great thunderous forte. When he had finished, the public gave him a great standing ovation.

textDisplay: I have played since I was 8 and performed live since I was 13. I am 61 now. Music has taken me places I never would have gone otherwise and allowed me to meet people I would not have met otherwise. My life has been so much richer, so much better because of music. My message to you is to keep playing music and never give up. Keep studying music, trying new things and express yourself in composing. After you become accomplished on the piano, try the guitar and the bass. Try singing and playing. Try recording. Make your albums and give them to your friends. Try an open mic night and entertain people. You will be amazed at how much your life improves. God bless you!
textOriginal: I have played since I was 8 and performed live since I was 13. I am 61 now. Music has taken me places I never would have gone otherwise and allowed me to meet people I would not have met otherwise. My life has been so much richer, so much better because of music. My message to you is to keep playing music and never give up. Keep studying music, trying new things and express yourself in composing. After you become accomplished on the piano, try the guitar and the bass. Try singing and playing. Try recording. Make your albums and give them to your friends. Try an open mic night and entertain people. You will be amazed at how much your life improves. God bless you!
